Achievements

Academic Progress.

As a first-year Information Technology student, I worked diligently to build a strong academic and practical foundation in the field. Although official semester one results are not yet released, I demonstrated steady commitment, growth, and engagement throughout the semester. Below are my key achievements:

Commitment to Academic Excellence

I maintained consistent attendance and actively participated in lectures, tutorials, and laboratory sessions. This helped me follow course content closely and strengthened my understanding of core IT principles.

Effective Use of Personal Laptop.

One of the most impactful contributions to my learning this semester was the personal laptop you generously provided. Having my own device greatly improved my ability to conduct research, practice programming, complete assignments on time, and revise materials at my own pace. This support has significantly enhanced my academic efficiency and independence.

Strong Engagement in Practical IT Work

I fully engaged in computer lab activities and practical coursework. These sessions enabled me to apply theoretical knowledge of hands-on tasks, improving both my confidence and technical competence.

  • Completed introductory programming exercises and small projects.
  • Performed basic hardware and software configuration tasks.
  • Learned the basic microsoft office application software packages.

Challenges.

Despite my overall progress, I encountered a few challenges during the semester that affected my studies. However, I worked hard to manage them and stay focused on my academic goals.

Health Challenges

During the semester, I fell sick with malaria, which temporarily affected my ability to attend classes and complete my work effectively. I am sincerely grateful for your support, which enabled me to receive treatment and recover quickly. Your assistance played a major role in helping me return to my studies without long-term setbacks.

Electrical power challenge.

One of the problems I faced was inadequate power because my room uses solar pannels which was frequently affected by whether changes. However, I tried to manage this by making sure that I charge my gadgets at campus though there's a lot of competition for the same service.

Academic Workload Adjustment

As a first-year IT student, adjusting to the increased workload and fast pace of the program was challenging. However, through better planning and consistent study habits, I managed to adapt and stay on track.

Balancing Practical and Theoretical Work

Some units required extensive practical work in addition to theory, which sometimes made time management difficult. I gradually improved by organizing my schedule and engaging in discussions with friends.

Semester one results update

I am pleased to share that I have successfully completed my end of semester examinations and academic requirements for semester one.The official release of the semester one results has been sheduled for the beginning of the next semester.Once they are published , I will share them immediately.

Beginning of semester two

Semester two was initially sheduled to begin in January; however, due to the Uganda national elections which would take place on 15th January, the start date may be pushed to early February. The University is currently monitoring the situation to ensure that academic activities resume smoothly and with minimal disruption. All official updates regarding the confirmed start date will be published on the student's portal, and I will continue to follow these announcements closely. Once the final date is confirmed, I will communicate about it accordingly.
